    "keywords" -> {
     "quantum mechanics", "quantum computation", "quantum information"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "ProductState[<|..., s -> {a, b}, ...|>] represents a product state, \
where the qubit s is in a linear combination Ket[0] a + Ket[1] b. \
ProductState[s -> {a, b}, ...] constructs and returns ProductState[<|s -> {a, \
b}, ...|>]. ProductState[..., {s1, s2, ...} -> {{a1, b1}, {a2, b2}, ...}, \
...] constructs ProductState[<|..., s1 -> {a1, b1}, s2 -> {a2, b2}, ...|>]. \
ProductState[..., {s1, s2, ...} -> {a, b}, ...] constructs \
ProductState[<|..., s1 -> {a, b}, s2 -> {a, b}, ...|>]. ProductState[spec, \
{s1, s2, ...}] or ProductState[spec, s] is equivalent to \
KetRegulate[ProductState[spec], {s1, s2, ...}]] or \
KetRegulate[ProductState[spec], {s}]. This is useful in specifying \
input/output state in QuantumCircuit.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, 
    "title" -> "ProductState", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "",
     "windowtitle" -> "ProductState", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
